WEBVTT

00:02:24.977 --> 00:02:30.590
and that the equitable distribution
of resources, services and access

00:02:30.614 --> 00:02:32.113
is a basic human right.

00:02:33.426 --> 00:02:35.301
So what does spatial justice look like?

00:02:36.161 --> 00:02:38.316
Well, I'd like to share a story with you.

00:02:39.703 --> 00:02:41.007
For years,

00:02:41.031 --> 00:02:44.188
I've been working in the historically
African-American neighborhood

00:02:44.212 --> 00:02:46.296
of Bayview Hunters Point in San Francisco,

00:02:46.320 --> 00:02:48.583
on a plot of land
that once held a power plant.

00:02:49.418 --> 00:02:50.645
Back in the '90s,

00:02:50.669 --> 00:02:53.739
a community group led by mothers
who lived in the public housing

00:02:53.763 --> 00:02:55.315
on the hill above the plant

00:02:55.339 --> 00:02:56.668
fought for its closure.

00:02:57.111 --> 00:02:58.261
They won.

00:02:58.592 --> 00:03:01.335
The utility company finally tore it down,